      <SubComponents>
        <Component class="javax.swing.JTextArea" name="jTextArea1">
          <Properties>
            <Property name="editable" type="boolean" value="false"/>
            <Property name="columns" type="int" value="20"/>
            <Property name="lineWrap" type="boolean" value="true"/>
            <Property name="rows" type="int" value="5"/>
            <Property name="text" type="java.lang.String" value="The turbine warmup procedure for cold start is designed to have the turbine spin up and synced to grid without the steam reheater, warming the high pressure part first. The steam drums pressure setpoint used for startup is defined as a function of thermal reactor output and can be viewed with a diagram representing it.&#xa;&#xa;Those are the designed turbine hold points with steam parameters and reactor power and the neutron flux setpoints.&#xa;&#xa;0750 1/min - 15 bar - 140 MWth - 4.7 %N&#xa;1500 1/min - 27 bar - 206 MWth - 7.0 %N&#xa;2250 1/min - 38 bar - 263 MWth - 8.8 %N&#xa;3000 1/min - 50 bar - 326 MWth - 10.9 %N&#xa;&#xa;It is not neccessary to have precisely those values.&#xa;&#xa;The turbine should be synced to grid with 50 bars. From a neutron setpoint of 13 %N, the pressure setpoint will be 64 bars.&#xa;&#xa;With 15 %N, start heating up the low pressure turbine by carefully using the steam reheater.&#xa;"/>
            <Property name="wrapStyleWord" type="boolean" value="true"/>
          </Properties>
        </Component>
      </SubComponents>
    </Container>
  </SubComponents>
